            "answer_text": "The Raspberry Pi Foundation has another madly reasonable PC that you can make things with. The Pi Zero costs an absurdly low $5 and is just as available, if somewhat more constrained, than its greater sibling. Similarly as we did with the Raspberry Pi 3, we made a little Kodi box out of the Pi Zero and in all honesty, it's astonishing something this modest can do a wonder such as this by any stretch of the imagination. ",
